5000|$|Along {{with other}} major faith <b>councils,</b> <b>Hindu</b> <b>Council</b> UK {{is invited to}} consult on Government policy {{from time to time}} [...] The {{consultation}} processes take place in agreement with the Inter Faith Network and <b>Hindu</b> <b>Council</b> UK input and feedback from a Hindu point of view. Various Government departments are involved, particularly the Home Office and Department for Innovation, Universities and Skills. In addition <b>Hindu</b> <b>Council</b> UK is represented at other government related bodies like the Equality and Human Rights Commission.|$|R
